<div class="social-facts">
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;">&nbsp;<span style="font-family: GraublauSans-Book, 'Lucida Sans', 'Lucida Grande', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">Tourism's economic Impact</span></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">- Revenues totaled over&nbsp;<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>$2.5B</strong></span>&nbsp;in 2010.<br /><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>- $1.18B</strong></span>&nbsp;came from non-resident visitors.</span><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"><br /></span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">- Generates&nbsp;<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>$260M</strong></span>&nbsp;in tax revenues annually.<br /><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; line-height: 21.333332061767578px;">- <span style="color: #000000;"><strong>2.1M</strong></span> visitors come to Nova Scotia each year.</span><br /></span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">- Tourism employs&nbsp;<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>40,000+</strong></span>&nbsp;Nova Scotians.<br />- <span style="color: #000000;"><strong>1</strong></span> out of&nbsp;<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>3</strong></span> Nova Scotians work in Tourism as their first job.&nbsp;</span></span></p>
</div>
